gomodel:SYNGO_3792  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Alk is postsynaptically localized at both subclasses of type I boutons. These are characterized by extensive postsynaptic subsynaptic reticulum (SSR; (Atwood, Govind et al. 1993; Jia, Gorczyca et al. 1993)), which harbors the postsynaptic scaffold Discs Large (Dlg) (Lahey, Gorczyca et al. 1994) and glutamate receptors (GluRs) (Fig. 1B,E).. Experimental description: M&M Drosophila Stocks:The jebko5644 and alk1null mutations have been fully described by us and others (Loren et al., 2001; Weiss et al.,2001), and were analyzed in our recent study (Rohrboughand Broadie, 2011)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-19" ;
